# matplotlib.axes.Axes.twinx

Axes.twinx()[source]

    
Create a twin Axes sharing the xaxis.

Create a new Axes with an invisible x-axis and an independent y-axis
positioned opposite to the original one (i.e. at right). The x-axis autoscale
setting will be inherited from the original Axes. To ensure that the tick
marks of both y-axes align, see `LinearLocator`.

Returns

    
Axes

    
The newly created Axes instance

#### Notes

For those who are 'picking' artists while using twinx, pick events are only
called for the artists in the top-most Axes.
